Description: PYEZMINC is a python module to read and write MINC files.

FEATURES:
- read/write MINC1 and MINC2 images from/to numpy array
- read metadata header
- 3 simple classes: 
  - Image (numpy.float64)
  - Label (numpy.int32)
  - Mask (numpy.int32)


BUILD REQUIREMENTS:
- python2-devel
- minc-toolkit >= 0.3.16
- Cython >= 0.17
- zlib-devel
- numpy
- scipy

HOW TO INSTALL:
python setup.py install

TODO:
- Write MINC header
- Read header only

TO INSTALL ON ANOTHER ENVIRONMENT:
step 1:
    conda env create -f environment.yml

step 2:
    conda activate pyezminc
    python setup.py install --mincdir /path/to/minc/enivornment/
    python setup.py sdist bdist_wheel --mincdir /path/to/minc/enivornment/

step 3:
    conda deactivate
    conda activate YOUR-ENV-NAME
    pip install /path/to/your/package/dist/your_package_name-version-***.whl
